{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"adf7732d2b92a9f2a438834b28b68197358112b2"},"timestamp":1400083994,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUzMzUwNzQxNw==","github-url":"https://github.com/parrot/parrot/issues/1070","origin":"github"},"title":"Compile error for parrot on FreeBSD with OpenGL/freeglut","message":"I don't think this is a parrot bug and can't think of a way it could be handled in the `Configure.pl` stage, but I am putting it here in case it bites others. Over several releases of freeglut and parrot the parrot build has stopped with \"`__APPLE__ not defined`\" when compiling `src/glut_callbacks.c` unless I remove the `#if` below.  I am using:\n- various recent parrots\n- freeglut-2.8.1_2\n- FreeBSD 9.2-RELEASE\n\n```\n--- /usr/local/include/GL/freeglut_std.h.orig    2014-05-13 13:58:24.082926992 -0400\n+++ /usr/local/include/GL/freeglut_std.h        2014-05-13 13:58:39.448952929 -0400\n@@ -121,13 +121,8 @@\n /*\n  * Always include OpenGL and GLU headers\n  */\n-#if __APPLE__\n-#   include \u003cOpenGL/gl.h\u003e\n-#   include \u003cOpenGL/glu.h\u003e\n-#else\n #   include \u003cGL/gl.h\u003e\n #   include \u003cGL/glu.h\u003e\n-#endif\n\n /*\n  * GLUT API macro definitions -- the special key codes:\n```\n\nOtherwise `--parrot-option='--without-opengl'` is needed.","files":null}]}